---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHead from "../../components/PageHead.astro";
import Tooltip from "../../components/Tooltip.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="It's Not You - It Might Be Your Machine"
  description="A quick checklist to help you troubleshoot common knitting machine issues—without blaming yourself."
>
  <div class="page-wrap troubleshoot-page-wrap">
    <header class="lm-hero">
   
      <div class="lm-hero__text">
        <h1>It's Not You — It Might Be Your Machine</h1>
        <p>
          When something goes wrong on a knitting machine, most knitters assume they did something wrong.
          Sometimes that's true - but many times the machine just needs a quick check.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="lm-well">
    <div class="lm-reset" aria-label="60-second reset">
      <h2>The 60-Second Reset</h2>
      <ul class="lm-resetList">
        <li><strong>Re-thread</strong> the yarn in the tension unit and carriage and make sure it feeds smoothly.</li>
        <li><strong>Reset</strong> the carriage to <Tooltip term="plain knitting">plain knitting </Tooltip> settings.</li>
        <li><strong>Test</strong> 10 rows with a smooth "known good" yarn.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You'd be surprised how often that alone fixes the problem.</p>
    </div>

    <section aria-label="5 things to check">
      <h2>5 Things to Check Before Blaming Your Machine</h2>

      <div class="lm-steps">
      <div class="lm-step">
        <div class="lm-step__header">
          <span class="lm-step__badge">1</span>
          <h3 class="lm-step__title">Yarn Path</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="lm-step__body">
          <div class="lm-stepGrid">
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__media">
              <figure class="lm-photo">
                <div class="lm-photo__label">What to look for</div>
                <img
                  src="/images/yarn-path.jpg"
                  alt="Yarn path example near the mast/tension area"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption>Yarn that snags, twists, or tightens suddenly can cause "mystery" drops.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__text">
              <p>If the yarn snags or feeds unevenly, the machine can't form consistent stitches. Even a small twist in the tension unit can cause dropped stitches.</p>
              <p><strong>You're looking for:</strong> yarn that feeds unevenly, jerks while knitting, or suddenly tightens.</p>
              <p><strong>Quick test:</strong> Pull the yarn gently and watch the full path to the needles.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="lm-divider" />

      <div class="lm-step">
        <div class="lm-step__header">
          <span class="lm-step__badge">2</span>
          <h3 class="lm-step__title">Needle Movement</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="lm-step__body">
          <div class="lm-stepGrid">
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__media">
              <div class="lm-mediaSpacer" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__text">
              <p>Every needle should slide freely. One sticky or bent needle can cause problems in the same spot again and again.</p>
              <p><strong>You're looking for:</strong> a needle that feels sticky, bent, or doesn't slide as smoothly as the others.</p>
              <p><strong>Quick test:</strong> Slide the needles by hand and feel for resistance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="lm-divider" />

      <div class="lm-step">
        <div class="lm-step__header">
          <span class="lm-step__badge">3</span>
          <h3 class="lm-step__title">Sponge Bar Pressure</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="lm-step__body">
          <div class="lm-stepGrid">
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__media">
              <figure class="lm-photo">
                <div class="lm-photo__label">What to look for</div>
                <img
                  src="/images/sponge-bar.jpg"
                  alt="Close-up of removing or inspecting the sponge bar"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption>Loose needles often point to sponge bar pressure.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__text">
              <p>A worn <Tooltip term="sponge bar">sponge bar</Tooltip> is one of the most common causes of mysterious knitting issues. If needles feel loose, the machine can't hold stitches reliably.</p>
              <p><strong>You're looking for:</strong> needles that feel loose, sit lower than normal, or don't stay firmly in position.</p>
              <p><strong>Quick test:</strong> Do the needles sit firmly in position?</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="lm-divider" />

      <div class="lm-step">
        <div class="lm-step__header">
          <span class="lm-step__badge">4</span>
          <h3 class="lm-step__title">Carriage Settings</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="lm-step__body">
          <div class="lm-stepGrid">
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__media">
              <div class="lm-mediaSpacer" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__text">
              <p>Sometimes a patterning setting is left on accidentally. One tiny lever can completely change how the machine knits.</p>
              <p><strong>You're looking for:</strong> a <Tooltip term="tuck">Tuck</Tooltip>, <Tooltip term="slip">Slip</Tooltip>, or <Tooltip term="holding position">Hold</Tooltip> button that may have been engaged accidentally.</p>
              <p><strong>Quick test:</strong> Reset everything to plain knit settings and try again.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="lm-divider" />

      <div class="lm-step">
        <div class="lm-step__header">
          <span class="lm-step__badge">5</span>
          <h3 class="lm-step__title">Yarn Compatibility</h3>
        </div>
        <div class="lm-step__body">
          <div class="lm-stepGrid">
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__media">
              <figure class="lm-photo">
                <div class="lm-photo__label">What to look for</div>
                <img
                  src="/images/yarn-path.jpg"
                  alt="Close-up of yarn types that may be fuzzy or uneven"
                  loading="lazy"
                />
                <figcaption>Fuzzy or uneven yarn can "fight" the machine even when you're doing everything right.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="lm-stepGrid__text">
              <p>Not every yarn behaves well on a knitting machine. Thick, fuzzy, or uneven yarns can create trouble even when you're doing everything right.</p>
              <p><strong>You're looking for:</strong> yarn that is fuzzy, uneven, thick, or hard for the machine to pull consistently.</p>
              <p><strong>Quick test:</strong> Try a smooth "known good" yarn to see if the problem disappears.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="note" aria-label="Reassurance">
      <h2>Remember This</h2>
      <p><strong>You didn't break your machine — and you're not alone.</strong></p>
      <p>
        Machine knitting has a lot of moving parts. Most issues come down to yarn flow, needle movement,
        or a setting that's easy to overlook.
      </p>
    </section>

    <hr class="lm-hairline" />
    <section class="lm-safetynet" aria-label="Still stuck safety net">
      <h2>Still stuck?</h2>
      <p>
        If none of the above solved the problem, it might be time for a pro to take a look. I keep a running list of <a href="/repairs" target="_blank">known repair shops</a> if you need a place to start.</p>
    </section>

    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    /* Override global .page-wrap top padding; Layout already supplies header clearance */
    .troubleshoot-page-wrap.page-wrap { padding-top: 8px; }

    .lm-well{
      background:#fff;
      border-radius:18px;
      padding:34px;
      margin-top:18px;
      box-shadow:0 14px 36px rgba(0,0,0,.10);
    }

    .lm-hero{
      display:flex;
      gap:14px;
      align-items:flex-start;
      margin-bottom:16px;
      padding-top:0.5rem;
    }
    .lm-hero__logo{
      flex:0 0 auto;
    }
    .lm-hero__text h1{
      margin-top:0;
    }

    .lm-reset{
      border:1px solid rgba(82,104,45,.22);
      border-left:4px solid #52682d;
      background:rgba(82,104,45,.06);
      border-radius:12px;
      padding:18px 20px;
      margin-bottom:22px;
    }
    .lm-reset h2{
      margin-top:0;
      margin-bottom:6px;
    }
    .lm-resetList{
      list-style:none;
      padding-left:0;
      margin:12px 0;
    }
    .lm-resetList li{
      position:relative;
      padding-left:26px;
      margin:6px 0;
    }
    .lm-resetList li::before{
      content:"✔";
      position:absolute;
      left:0;
      top:0;
      font-weight:700;
      color:#52682d;
      opacity:.85;
    }

    .lm-stepGrid{
      display:grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(240px, 360px) 1fr;
      gap:18px;
      align-items:center;
    }
    .lm-stepGrid__media{
      display:flex;
      justify-content:flex-start;
    }
    .lm-stepGrid__text{
      min-width:0;
    }
    .lm-mediaSpacer{
      width:100%;
      max-width:340px;
      min-height:220px;
      visibility:hidden;
    }

    .lm-photo{
      margin:0 !important;
      margin-top:0 !important;
      align-self:start !important;
      max-width:340px;
      justify-self:start;
      border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.12);
      border-radius:14px;
      overflow:hidden;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.10);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.7);
    }
    .lm-photo__label{
      font-weight:700;
      padding:10px 12px;
      border-bottom:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.10);
    }
    .lm-photo img{
      display:block;
      width:100%;
      height:auto;
      object-fit:cover;
    }
    .lm-photo figcaption{
      padding:10px 12px 12px;
      opacity:.85;
      font-size:0.95rem;
    }

    .lm-steps{
      position:relative;
      padding-left:14px;
    }
    .lm-steps::before{
      content:"";
      position:absolute;
      left:6px;
      top:10px;
      bottom:10px;
      width:2px;
      background:rgba(82,104,45,.18);
    }
    .lm-step{
      position:relative;
      border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.10);
      border-radius:14px;
      overflow:hidden;
      background:#fff;
      margin: 14px 0;
    }
    .lm-step__badge{
      display:inline-flex;
      align-items:center;
      justify-content:center;
      width:28px;
      height:28px;
      border-radius:999px;
      background:#fff;
      color:#52682d;
      font-weight:700;
      font-size:.9rem;
    }
    .lm-step__header{
      background:#52682d;
      color:#fff;
      padding:14px 18px;
      display:flex;
      align-items:center;
      gap:12px;
      margin-left:6px;
    }
    .lm-step__title{
      margin:0;
      font-size:1.1rem;
      line-height:1.3;
      color:#fff !important;
    }
    .lm-step__body{
      padding:14px;
    }
    .lm-divider{
      border:0;
      border-top:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.08);
      margin:14px 0;
    }

    .lm-hairline{
      border:0;
      border-top:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.10);
      margin:18px 0;
    }
    .lm-safetynet h2{
      margin-top:0;
    }
    .lm-safetynet a{
      color:#52682d;
      font-weight:700;
      text-decoration:underline;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }
    .lm-safetynet a:hover{
      text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 820px){
      .lm-stepGrid{
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap:12px;
      }
      .lm-mediaSpacer{
        display:none;
      }
      .lm-photo{
        max-width:420px;
        justify-self:stretch;
      }
      .lm-step__header{ padding:12px; }
      .lm-step__body{ padding:12px; }
      .lm-well{
        padding:22px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
